<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="109" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="22" pageNumber="109">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="22" pageNumber="109">Subdepressed to dorsally convex; testaceous to rufous; mentum bearing paired circular foveae; foretibia notched apicolaterally; basal protarsomere of male dilated, medially dentiform; mesepisternum with or without small fovea; elytral strial interneurs varied in form, punctate to striatiopunctate; i8 apically curvy, diverted medially at Eo5-6 and Eo7; ARG short and arcuate or rudimentary and continuous with i3. ABL = 1.2-4.6 mm.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
